The magnetic field of the spectrometer

Both 12C and 13C targets were used in the experiment.
Since the 12C and 13C scattered protons could not be
separated at the small scattering angles the number
of counts had to be corrected for the 12C present.
Both a normal carbon target and 13C enriched target
were placed on the target backing. The target backing
could be raised or lowered so that the two foils
could be alternately placed in the proton beam.
